  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations. All thirteen credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels in this accepted package. Three validation results are recorded, including one high-fidelity bench-top hemolysis correlation study whose generation activity is described in detail in the accompanying narrative but whose structured provenance link is absent from the structured record.",
