    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/experimental-hemolysis-correlation-vr002",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-top hemolysis correlation against FDA generic pump experimental data — five operating points",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
      "description": "A series of bench-top hemolysis experiments were conducted at the sponsor's in-house hemocompatibility laboratory using a physical replica of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. Bovine blood at controlled hematocrit (38 ± 2%) was circulated for 120-minute test intervals at each of the five target flow-speed combinations (2 L/min at 2400 RPM, 3 L/min at 2600 RPM, 4 L/min at 2800 RPM, 5 L/min at 3000 RPM, and 6 L/min at 3200 RPM). Plasma-free hemoglobin was measured by the modified Drabkin spectrophotometric method at 15-minute intervals. The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) was computed per ASTM F1841. CFD-predicted NIH values, obtained by post-processing shear-stress exposure histories along 50 000 massless tracer particles seeded uniformly at the inlet, were compared against the mean experimental NIH at each operating point. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen coefficients) was applied. Predicted NIH fell within ±18% of measured NIH at four of five operating points; the 5 L/min condition showed a 24% over-prediction, attributed to secondary flow structures near the volute cutwater that are sensitive to turbulence model selection. This result is considered acceptable at MRL 5 given the conservative direction of the discrepancy. The study was conducted during Q3 2024 and the raw data are archived under accession HEMO-2024-COU2-FDA in the sponsor's document management system."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/monte-carlo-uq-coverage-vr003",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ coverage verification — 95th-percentile NIH envelope",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-hemolysis-samples-5op-points",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/monte-carlo-uq-run-10000samples-2025"
    }
  ],
