      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments performed on the same pump geometry, same fluid, same operating range as COU; any differences in geometry or fluid properties documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same geometry as the COU. Fluid was bovine blood rather than human blood; species differences in RBC fragility are documented but not fully quantified, preventing achievement of level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residuals below 1e-6 for all equations; round-off error analysis documented; solver settings frozen across all production runs.",
      "rationale": "Residuals converged to 1e-5 for continuity and momentum; the hemolysis scalar equation converged to 1e-4 due to stiff source terms. Round-off error analysis was not performed. Achieved level 3 falls short of required level 4."
