      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection justified by physics-based arguments and sensitivity studies; alternative model forms evaluated.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on prior literature for rotating machinery. A sensitivity study comparing SST k-omega against realizable k-epsilon was performed at one operating point only. The Giersiepen hemolysis power-law model was used without evaluation of alternative damage accumulation models. Achieved level 3 is significantly below required level 5."
    },
    {
