      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterised with uncertainty bounds; sensitivity analysis identifies dominant inputs; uncertain inputs propagated through Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 10 000 samples propagating uncertainty in blood viscosity, inlet flow rate, and Giersiepen model coefficients. Pump geometry tolerances and surface roughness were not included in the UQ; these are identified as dominant contributors in the literature, limiting achieved level to 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum of three independent blood sample lots per operating point; donor variability characterised; statistical power analysis supports sample size.",
      "rationale": "A single bovine blood lot was used across all five operating points. Inter-lot variability in RBC fragility was not characterised. No statistical power analysis was performed to justify sample size. Achieved level 2 is well below required level 4, representing a significant credibility gap."
    },
